{"type":"message","id":"312a9062","parentId":"9e3e4a39","timestamp":"2026-05-15T07:44:06.811Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Interesting - the sub-agent is still running and actively investigating. It found that the pipeline DID execute - `RunHotUpdatePipeline` was called, `PipelineBuildAssetBundle` was started, etc. The pipeline steps appear to have started but we need to see if they completed.\n\nThe log ends with SpriteAtlasPacking. This might mean the build of asset bundles ran but the subsequent CDN upload steps may not have been reached yet.\n\nBut wait - Unity exited (the process is gone), and the bat echoed exit code. Let me see what happened with the sub-agent more recently - it seems like it's been running for about 23 minutes. Let me check more recent messages.\n\nActually, looking at timestamps - the sub-agent started at 1778829590 (15:39:50) and the latest message I see is at 1778831039 (15:43:59). It's been running for about 4 minutes since that message.\n\nBut wait, the sub-agent process (agent:main:subagent:65b5d2a1) was spawned with mode \"run\" - it should auto-announce when done. Let me just wait for it rather than spying on it. But the master (Yousan) is asking NOW about whether it's done.\n\nLet me just check the process exec session that ran the bat directly to see if it has the exit code. Actually let me check the log file to look for \"Exit\" or return code markers.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_taQUz0gAXaCmiS47JhRg1043","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Select-String -Path \"E:\\Solo\\nightoffullmoon\\client\\cardv\\BuildPipeline_RunHotUpdate.log\" -Pattern \"(Exit|exit|quit|Quit|Return|return|Done|done|Complete|complete)\" | Select-Object -Last 10","timeout":10}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":1218,"output":428,"cacheRead":52736,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":54382,"cost":{"input":0.0001705