{"type":"message","id":"d46b0b06","parentId":"2cb345e7","timestamp":"2026-05-15T07:44:16.169Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The log ends at line 359704 and only shows SpriteAtlasPacking completed messages - no \"Done\", \"Exit\", \"Finished\", or any pipeline completion marker. This strongly suggests the Unity process was killed or crashed before it finished the pipeline.\n\nWait - but earlier I saw that Unity exited with \"Cleanup mono\" in the Editor.log. And I also checked that the bat file echoes the exit code. But we capture the bat's stdout through the exec session. The sub-agent ran the exec command that launched the bat, so the exit code would be in the exec output.\n\nLet me actually wait for the sub-agent to finish rather than keep polling. But the master is asking for status NOW. Let me check the sub-agent's most recent session history to see if it found anything new.\n\nActually, I saw the latest message from the sub-agent was:\n- It called exec with `Select-String -Pattern \"BuildAssetBundle|BuildPipeline|ExecuteStep|Pipeline\"` \n- And got back pipeline debug info showing the pipeline DID start\n\nThe sub-agent is still processing. I could just check myself directly - let me check if there's a CDN package generated to know if the CDN step completed.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_QrXCpxZoNQiQjBEEPWIu2884","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Get-ChildItem \"D:\\cdn_solo\" -Directory -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Select-Object Name, LastWriteTime | Sort-Object LastWriteTime -Descending | Select-Object -First 5","timeout":5}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":540,"output":354,"cacheRead":54272,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":55166,"cost":{"input":0.00007560000000000001,"output":0.00009912000000000001,"cacheRead":0.001519616,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0016943359999999998}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778