{"type":"message","id":"a81a0e73","parentId":"f824d1d2","timestamp":"2026-05-15T07:44:29.977Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"There's a Unity crash at 11:49 today! But the current run was from 15:39 onwards - that crash was from earlier (probably the Unity Editor that was open, PID 20280, being killed).\n\nWait - earlier I ran `Get-Process Unity` and it didn't show the PID 20280 Unity.exe anymore. Let me check if the PID 20280's Unity crash was from when I killed it or if it crashed on its own.\n\nActually, looking more carefully at the crash time `2026-05-15_034911255` with LastWriteTime `2026/5/15 11:49:11` - this was from when the Unity Editor was killed (the previous attempt's cleanup maybe).\n\nFor the current hot update pipeline run (bat execution from 15:39 onwards), Unity started, ran build asset bundles (which takes time), and then... it seems to have exited without completing the CDN upload. But I don't see a crash dump for the current run.\n\nLet me just kill the sub-agent and report what I know. The CDN didn't get updated, and the Unity process is gone. Let me get more info by checking if the AB1 or AB2 directories on the CDN server were touched.\n\nActually, let me re-think. The sub-agent is still running and investigating. It's been 23 minutes and the sub-agent is actively polling. Let me kill it and do my own thorough check.\n\nLet me just check the bat output directly - the exec process that ran the bat.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_U9xgqOke3L3hko7U25br0014","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# 直接看 bat 的输出，或者检查 Unity 进程退出后留下的线索\n# 检查 Bundles 是否构建成功\nGet-ChildItem \"E:\\Solo\\nightoffullmoon\\client\\cardv\\AssetBundles\" -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Select-Object Name, LastWriteTime | Sort-Object LastWriteTime -Descending | Select-Object -First 5","timeout":5}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":202,