{"type":"message","id":"7ed59652","parentId":"1d04b23d","timestamp":"2026-05-15T07:44:38.323Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"That process session is from the sub-agent's sandbox, not from the main agent. I can't access it.\n\nLet me just kill the sub-agent and report what happened - it seems like the Unity process either crashed or was killed during the build. The CDN directory wasn't updated, no asset bundles directory exists. The pipeline didn't complete.\n\nActually, wait - let me check if there was another Editor.log for the batchmode session. When Unity runs with `-logFile`, it writes to that file. The Editor.log from the batchmode might also have info. But this Editor.log might have gotten overwritten.\n\nLet me try one more thing - check the log for \"Started\" or \"End\" type messages to understand how far the pipeline got.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_keCZpIM9PK3XeEjSSgdQ3194","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Select-String -Path \"E:\\Solo\\nightoffullmoon\\client\\cardv\\BuildPipeline_RunHotUpdate.log\" -Pattern \"^(Started|End|Step|Build|Begin|Finish)\" | Select-Object -Last 10","timeout":10}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":99,"output":268,"cacheRead":56192,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":56559,"cost":{"input":0.000013860000000000001,"output":0.00007504,"cacheRead":0.001573376,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.001662276}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778831074027,"responseId":"28a9f0f3-57d6-495f-ad0c-4836308c1e9c"}}
