{"type":"message","id":"ab5c8d03","parentId":"8b60a3e9","timestamp":"2026-05-15T07:44:45.764Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK so the pipeline DID start:\n1. Line 1100: `BuildPipeline.RunHotUpdatePipeline (batch, all steps): '热更'` - started\n2. Line 1109: `BuildPipeline CLI (batch) mode=Full pipeline='热更'` \n3. Line 349852-349853: `BuildPlayerGenerator: Succeeded` (this seems to be from multiple builds)\n4. Line 355427: `BuildPlayerGenerator: Succeeded`\n5. Line 355429: `BuildPlayer: start building target 19`\n6. Line 356225: `BuildPlayerGenerator: Succeeded`\n\nThen later SpriteAtlasPacking messages follow (around line 359k+). The log file ends at line 359704 with SpriteAtlasPacking.\n\nSo the pipeline:\n- ✅ Started the \"热更\" pipeline\n- ✅ BuildPlayerGenerator succeeded multiple times\n- ✅ Started building target 19\n- ✅ SpriteAtlasPacking was happening at the end\n\nBut the log just... ends. No completion message. No error message. This is suspicious - it seems like Unity was killed (possibly the bat process timed out?).\n\nWait - the sub-agent ran the exec with a timeout of 3600 (1 hour) and yieldMs of 60000 (60 seconds). So it had plenty of time.\n\nBut maybe the Unity process crashed or was killed by OOM or some other reason. Let me check the log more carefully - specifically right before the final SpriteAtlasPacking lines.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_P67HAb4LEgkSW0AFKbUe2778","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Get-Content \"E:\\Solo\\nightoffullmoon\\client\\cardv\\BuildPipeline_RunHotUpdate.log\" -Tail 15 | Select-Object -First 5; Write-Output \"=== BEFORE LAST 15 ===\"; Get-Content \"E:\\Solo\\nightoffullmoon\\client\\cardv\\BuildPipeline_RunHotUpdate.log\" -Tail 50 | Select-Object -First 35","timeout":5}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":458,"output":474,"cacheRead":56448,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":573