{"type":"message","id":"15bc2338","parentId":"e29fca39","timestamp":"2026-05-15T07:44:51.677Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK the log just ends with SpriteAtlasPacking. No completion message, no error. The bat file uses `-logFile` which directs ALL Unity output to that file - including any crashes. The log just ending abruptly like this suggests the Unity process was killed or crashed.\n\nBut I also need to check - earlier when I ran `Get-Process Unity` it showed no Unity process was running. Let me check again now.\n\nWait - the Editor.log I checked earlier had:\n```\n[Licensing::IpcConnector] License Notification channel disconnected successfully.\n[Licensing::IpcConnector] License Client channel disconnected successfully.\nAcceleratorClientConnectionCallback - disconnected - :0\nCleanup mono\ndebugger-agent: Unable to listen on 12492\n```\n\nBut this might be from a DIFFERENT Unity session (the earlier Editor that was running). Since both batchmode and editor share the same Editor.log path, they overwrite each other.\n\nLet me check the timestamps on the log file.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_QDlcy1VPUKgsAFIjiOTg5494","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Get-Item \"E:\\Solo\\nightoffullmoon\\client\\cardv\\BuildPipeline_RunHotUpdate.log\" | Select-Object Length, LastWriteTime, CreationTime; Write-Output \"===\"; Get-Item \"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\AppData\\Local\\Unity\\Editor\\Editor.log\" | Select-Object Length, LastWriteTime, CreationTime","timeout":5}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":502,"output":352,"cacheRead":57344,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":58198,"cost":{"input":0.00007028000000000001,"output":0.00009856,"cacheRead":0.001605632,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.001774472}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778831086777,"responseId":"5d8d6faf-8692-49af-8f5f-f03769fb845e"}}
