{"type":"message","id":"b5a041f3","parentId":"354b3e1b","timestamp":"2026-05-15T07:45:03.142Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The build pipeline log was last written at 15:34:26 - that was the PREVIOUS run (the first attempt that failed because Unity Editor was open)! \n\nThe Editor.log was last written at 15:40:55 - this is from the Editor GUI session (PID 20280) which was running interactively.\n\nSo the current batch run's log file was created at 11:49:08 - that's from the crash event. The bat file uses the same log file path, so it should have OVERWRITTEN or APPENDED to it. Let me check if there's a new log being generated for the current run.\n\nWait - the log file was last written at 15:34:26, but the current bat execution started at around 15:39:50. If the bat was executed successfully, the log file should have been modified after that time. The fact that it wasn't modified (15:34) means the bat executed but the Unity process didn't actually start piping output, or Unity exited immediately without writing anything new.\n\nWait no - the log file LastWriteTime is 15:34:26 from the PREVIOUS run. The current bat execution started at ~15:39 - if Unity ran successfully, it would have either overwritten or appended to this file. The LastWriteTime is still 15:34, which means the current batchmode Unity didn't write to this file.\n\nBut the sub-agent's investigation showed content in the log file with BuildPipeline entries... let me re-read the situation.\n\nActually, looking at the sub-agent's output again:\n- It ran `Select-String -Pattern \"BuildAssetBundle|BuildPipeline|ExecuteStep|Pipeline\"` and got results including:\n  - `BuildPipeline.RunHotUpdatePipeline (batch, all steps): '热更'`\n  - `BuildPlayerGenerator: Succeeded`\n  - `BuildPlayer: start building target 19`\n  \nBut all these are at line numbers below 360k in a file with 359704 lines. The Log LastWriteTime is 15:34 from the PREVIOUS run.\n\nSo the current bat execution that started at ~15:39... where did its output go?\n\nWait, I think I'm confusing two different runs:\n1. **First run** (earlier today, ~15:30): The sub-agent that failed because Unity Editor was open (PID 20280). This run was from 小骑士's first request.\n2. **Second run** (now): The current sub-agent running from 小骑士's second request.\n\nThe log file LastWriteTime 15:34 was from the FIRST run. The second run started at ~15:39. Since the second bat execution was given a fresh task, it would have been executed using `exec` in the sub-agent's sandbox.\n\nBut looking at the sub-agent's history, it DID find pipeline content in the log. So the first run's output is still in the log file. The second run's output might also have been appended.\n\nActually, let me check the log file size and see if it grew since the second run started.\n\nThe log file is 37605732 bytes - let me check its current size now.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_1ppKoOUWAUV0ovavXtcV1140","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Get-Item \"E:\\Solo\\nightoffullmoon\\client\\cardv\\BuildPipeline_RunHotUpdate.log\" | Select-Object Length, LastWriteTime","timeout":3}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":180,"output":763,"cacheRead":58112,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":59055,"cost":{"input":0.000025200000000000003,"output":0.00021364000000000002,"cacheRead":0.001627136,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.001865976}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778831092597,"responseId":"8690d764-d269-4b6d-8f5e-d105ccda31be"}}
