{"type":"message","id":"f4425c2b","parentId":"c36498a0","timestamp":"2026-05-15T07:45:21.469Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Log file hasn't changed since 15:34. The bat was executed at ~15:39. That means the Unity process either:\n1. Didn't start at all\n2. Started but crashed immediately without writing to the log\n3. The exec process in the sub-agent's sandbox didn't actually run the bat\n\nWait - I need to re-check the timestamps more carefully. The sub-agent `65b5d2a1` was spawned at 1778829590289 which translates to... let me calculate.\n\nFrom session_status earlier today at message om_x100b6f58a896388cb27aa3cf1200bca, timestamps:\n- Current time in the message was \"15:42 GMT+8\"\n- sub-agent started at `1778829590289` ms\n\nLet me look at my earlier output:\n`sessionStatus.query.session.sessionStatus.current timestamp: timestamp=1778816952448`\n\nSo 1778816952448 was around 15:49 on 2026-05-15... hmm, let me check.\n\nActually, the first sub-agent (849afa9c) runtime was reported as 16s. The second one (65b5d2a1) was started at 1778829590289.\n\nLet me check the difference: 1778829590289 - 1778816952448 = 12637784 ms = ~3.5 hours? That doesn't seem right.\n\nActually, these are Unix timestamps in milliseconds. Let me convert:\n1778829590289 ms → 1778829590.289 seconds → the actual date...\n\nUnix timestamp 1778829590 seconds → Let's calculate: \n- Current year is 2026\n- 1778829590 / (365.25*24*3600) ≈ 56.37 years since 1970 → 2026.37\n- So 1778829590 → approximately May 15, 2026\n\nLet me calculate more precisely:\nJanuary 1970 to January 2026 = 56 years = 56*365.25*24*3600 = 1767225600 seconds\n1778829590 - 1767225600 = 11603990 seconds since Jan 1, 2026\n\nJan 2026: 31 days = 2678400 seconds\nFeb 2026: 28 days = 2419200 seconds  \nMar 2026: 31 days = 2678400 seconds\nApr 2026: 30 days = 2592000 seconds\nTotal: 2678400+2419200+2678400+2592000 = 10368000 seconds\n\n11603990 - 10368000 = 1235990 seconds into May\n1235990 / 86400 = 14.3... → May 15\n1235990 mod 86400 = 14.3*86400... Let's do:\n14*86400 = 1209600\n1235990 - 1209600 = 26390 seconds into May 15\n26390 / 3600 = 7.33 hours = 7:20 AM\n0.33*60 ≈ 20 minutes\n\nSo the second sub-agent started at approximately 2026-05-15 07:20 UTC = 07:20 + 8 = 15:20 Beijing time.\n\nAnd the log file was last modified at 15:34. So the log file was modified AFTER the sub-agent started! But that was from the first run... \n\nActually, let me think again - the FIRST sub-agent (849afa9c) ran at about 15:10-15:11-ish. It failed and reported back. Then I replied in the group. Then 主人 said \"以后需要跑流水线都先关闭unity\" at some point. Then 小骑士 said \"更新测试服\" again. I replied and started the process.\n\nSo the timeline is:\n1. First 更新测试服 request from 小骑士 → sub-agent ran bat → failed because Unity Editor open → reported at ~15:20\n2. 主人 said to close Unity first → I updated TOOLS.md\n3. Second 更新测试服 request from 小骑士 → I checked + git pulled + spawned sub-agent at ~15:39\n\nThe log LastWriteTime is 15:34 which is between the two runs. This was probably from the FIRST run's batchmode Unity starting and then getting an error because the Editor was open.\n\nBut in the second run, Unity would try to start in batchmode and should write to the same log file... unless it's failing differently.\n\nActually, let me just check if Unity.exe is running right now or any process that was spawned by the bat.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_MXFBCt7Sibu8zlQeniq58101","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Get-CimInstance Win32_Process -Filter \"Name = 'Unity.exe'\" | Select-Object ProcessId, CommandLine; Write-Output \"=== CMD ===\"; Get-CimInstance Win32_Process -Filter \"Name = 'cmd.exe'\" | Where-Object { $_.CommandLine -like '*BuildPipeline*' -or $_.CommandLine -like '*hot*' } | Select-Object ProcessId, CommandLine","timeout":5}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":88,"