king.\n\nThen Unity exited, and the bat printed \"Unity 退出码: ...\" and returned.\n\nBut then PID 23816 started at 15:34:31. That was 5 seconds after the log stopped. This is likely a new Unity Editor instance being started by something - maybe Unity Hub, or maybe the user opened Unity manually.\n\nActually, now I think about it more carefully - perhaps PID 23816 was the start of a second stage of the pipeline. Let me check if the bat file or the pipeline launches multiple Unity processes for different platforms. But the bat only has a single Unity invocation.\n\nWait - I also checked earlier:\n```\nGet-Process | Where-Object { $_.ProcessName -match \"Unity|cmd|bat\" }\n```\nAnd found `cmd` process from 10:19:54. That's a command prompt window from the morning, not related.\n\nLet me try one more thing - search the log for the word \"error\" or \"exception\" near the end, and see if there's an out-of-memory or disk-full error."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_1Vnplbx8S1e2SuKQbNcE9042","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Select-String -Path \"E:\\Solo\\nightoffullmoon\\client\\cardv\\BuildPipeline_RunHotUpdate.log\" -Pattern \"out of memory|outofmemory|disk full|diskfull|IOException"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","stopReason":"aborted","timestamp":1778831114184,"responseId":"03afa199-17cd-48c1-a2e4-93e3d8866a8d","errorMessage":"Request was aborted","__openclaw":{"id":"fad74376","seq":39}}],"truncated":true,"droppedMessages":false,"contentTruncated":true,"contentRedacted":false,"bytes":3290},"isError":false,"timestamp":1778831132374}}
