{"type":"message","id":"9955f50d","parentId":"8dc3cd5b","timestamp":"2026-05-15T07:45:58.585Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK so the Unity installation is at `2020.3.49f1` not `2020.3.49f1c1`. The bat file correctly points to `2020.3.49f1`. \n\nBut the sub-agent mentioned it changed from `f1c1` to `f1`. Maybe the sub-agent was looking at the wrong path or misread the bat. Anyway, the bat path is correct now.\n\nNow - the actual issue is: what happened to the Unity batchmode process? The sub-agent found Unity PID 17676 ran at 15:20:56, built things, and then stopped at 15:34:26. The log shows SpriteAtlasPacking. Then Unity exited.\n\nThen a second Unity PID 23816 appeared at 15:34:31. This might have been the same Editor that was previously killed, restarting.\n\nBut actually - the sub-agent ran the bat via Start-Process inside the sub-agent's sandbox. The bat launched Unity which then exited. The bat should have printed \"Unity 退出码: ...\" after Unity exited. We need to see that exit code.\n\nSince the sub-agent timed out, and the log file stopped at 15:34... I need to check if the running bat process is still around.\n\nActually, I killed the sub-agent. Let me just look at what's happening now.\n\nThe bottom line: it's been running for 25 minutes. The log hasn't been updated since 15:34. No Unity processes running. CDN wasn't updated. It seems the pipeline failed.\n\nLet me check one more thing - let me look for any Unity Editor process that might have been opened and check the Editor.log for the batchmode run.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"Unity 进程已经没了，日志停在 15:34。让我看看最终状态。"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_YymRWzURQqaz7znIs83E8070","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Get-Process -Name \"Unity*\" -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Format-Table Id, ProcessName, StartTime; Write-Output \"=== LOG FILE ===\"; Get-Item \"E:\\Solo\\nightoffullmoon\\client\\cardv\\BuildPipeline_RunHotUpdate.log\" | Select-Object Length, LastWriteTime; Write-Output \"=== CDN DIR ===\"; Get-ChildItem \"D:\\cdn_solo\" -Directory -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Sort-Object LastWriteTime -Descending | Select-Object Name, LastWriteTime | Select-Object -First 3","timeout":5}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":51,"output":569,"cacheRead":64256,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":64876,"cost":{"input":0.00000714,"output":0.00015932,"cacheRead":0.0017991679999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0019656279999999996}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778831150062,"responseId":"15ded3cc-8429-4c12-9e10-669f60222f12"}}
{"type":"message","id":"c05083bc","parentId":"9955f50d","timestamp":"2026-05-15T07:45:59.420Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_YymRWzURQqaz7znIs83E8070","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Id ProcessName            StartTime         \r\n   -- -----------            ---------         \r\n 6844 Unity Hub              2026/5/15 10:19:51\r\n14828 Unity Hub              2026/5/15 10:19:52\r\n15164 Unity Hub              2026/5/15 10:19:52\r\n17428 Unity Hub              2026/5/15 10:19:52\r\n17752 Unity Hub              2026/5/15 10:19:54\r\n18216 Unity Hub              2026/5/15 10:19:54\r\n 6764 Unity.Licensing.Client 2026/5/15 10:19:53\r\n\r\n\r\n=== LOG FILE ===\r\n\r\n  Length LastWriteTime     \r\n  ------ -------------     \r\n37605732 2026/5/15 15:34:26\r\n=== CDN DIR ===\r\n         2026/3/13 11:37:54\r\n         2026/3/13 11:09:13\r\n         2026/3/13 10:15:01"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":761,"aggregated":"Id ProcessName            StartTime         \r\n   -- -----------            ---------         \r\n 6844 Unity Hub              2026/5/15 10:19:51\r\n14828 Unity Hub              2026/5/15 10:19:52\r\n15164 Unity Hub              2026/5/15 10:19:52\r\n17428 Unity Hub              2026/5/15 10:19:52\r\n17752 Unity Hub              2026/5/15 10:19:54\r\n18216 Unity Hub              2026/5/15 10:19:54\r\n 6764 Unity.Licensing.Client 2026/5/15 10:19:53\r\n\r\n\r\n=== LOG FILE ===\r\n\r\n  Length LastWriteTime     \r\n  ------ -------------     \r\n37605732 2026/5/15 15:34:26\r\n=== CDN DIR ===\r\n         2026/3/13 11:37:54\r\n         2026/3/13 11:09:13\r\n         2026/3/13 10:15:01","cwd":"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1778831159420}}
{"type":"message","id":"cb74c261","parentId":"c05083bc","timestamp":"2026-05-15T07:46:04.358Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK so:\n- No Unity Editor process running (only Unity Hub, Licensing Client)\n- Log file last modified at 15:34:26\n- CDN last modified in March (long ago)\n\nThe Unity batch process ran, did some work (built asset bundles), but then exited without completing the CDN upload step. The log ends with SpriteAtlasPacking.\n\nBut wait - the Editor.log might have info. Let me also check about the \"another Unity instance\" issue. Maybe the batchmode Unity started, but then the user's Unity Editor (which I thought I killed) was reopening...\n\nActually, let me check the Editor.log for more info. But the Editor.log might have been overwritten by the batchmode instance since batchmode Unity writes to the same Editor.log.\n\nLet me try a different approach - let me search for exit codes or completion info in the Editor.log file.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_v4ff9uJILiOxszFhuD029177","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Select-String -Path \"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\AppData\\Local\\Unity\\Editor\\Editor.log\" -Pattern \"(exit code|Exit code|exiting|Aborting)\" | Select-Object -Last 5","timeout":10}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":370,"output":292,"cacheRead":64768,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":65430,"cost":{"input":0.000051800000000000005,"output":0.00008176,"cacheRead":0.0018135039999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0019470639999999999}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778831159422,"responseId":"518b4a10-8959-4c6f-9ce8-cc4fea3874db"}}
