{"type":"message","id":"6709a9e6","parentId":"be369ef5","timestamp":"2026-05-15T12:50:09.504Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Some cookies are valid (tapdsession, t_u, t_cloud_login, _t_crop, t_i_token, _t_uid, new_worktable) but some are expired. The most important one is `tapdsession` which is still valid until May 22. Let me try loading the TAPD page to see if the session is still good.\n\nBut I still don't have 谭佳钦(小骑士)'s TAPD user ID. Let me check if I can find it by loading the TAPD page first and looking at the user list. Or maybe I can just use the name string and let TAPD handle the autocomplete.\n\nActually, let me look at the create_bug.mjs script again. It sets the handler via:\n```javascript\nconst h = document.querySelector('#BugCurrentOwner');\nif (h) { h.value = id; h.dispatchEvent(new Event('change', { bubbles: true })); }\n```\n\nThis sets the value directly. But TAPD's handler field is typically a user-select dropdown/autocomplete. Setting the value directly might not trigger the autocomplete properly.\n\nLet me try a different approach - first load the TAPD page to check login status, then figure out the user ID for 谭佳钦.\n\nLet me write a quick Playwright script that:\n1. Loads the TAPD bug creation page\n2. Checks if logged in\n3. If yes, creates the bug\n\nBut first I need 谭佳钦's user ID. Let me search the workspace files for it.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_81FwjP8X4axtrODypP037553","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Select-String -Path \"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\workspace\\*\" -Pattern \"谭佳钦|小骑士\" -SimpleMatch | Select-Object FileName, LineNumber, Line","timeout":10}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":757,"output":434,"cacheRead":71936,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":73127,"cost":{"input":0.00010598000000000001,"output":0.00012152,"cacheRead":0.002014208,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.002241708}