{"type":"message","id":"f29feae8","parentId":"65d2b1d9","timestamp":"2026-05-15T12:54:39.338Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The `.tt-dropdown-menu` wasn't found - the dropdown closed between page load and inspection. Let me try a different approach - I know the dropdown class is `.tt-dropdown-menu` from earlier output. But actually, the issue is that when I inspect the page, the dropdown might have disappeared.\n\nLet me take a different and simpler approach. Let me:\n1. Check what user ID the autocomplete actually returns by intercepting network requests or checking the hidden field more carefully\n2. Or better yet, directly use the API to set the handler\n\nActually, let me look at this differently. The autocomplete works and shows 谭佳钦. But when clicked, the hidden field gets \"谭佳钦;\" instead of a numeric ID. This might actually be acceptable - maybe the form accepts name strings in the hidden field too?\n\nThe form is still on the same page after clicking submit. This could be because:\n1. The handler value is invalid\n2. The submit button is an `<a>` tag, not an actual submit\n3. There's a different validation issue\n\nLet me try submitting directly via JavaScript by submitting the form programmatically.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_4gZ48WYgzcfP6vh0NgcU7711","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"import { chromium } from 'playwright';\nimport fs from 'fs';\nimport path from 'path';\nimport { fileURLToPath } from 'url';\n\nconst __filename = fileURLToPath(import.meta.url);\nconst __dirname = path.dirname(__filename);\nconst COOKIES_FILE = path.join(__dirname, 'tapd_cookies.json');\nconst WORKSPACE_ID = '31253609';\n\nconst STEALTH_INIT = () => {\n  delete navigator.webdriver;\n  Object.defineProperty(navigator, 'webdriver', { get: () => false });\n  Object.defineProperty(navigator, 'plugins', { get: () => [1, 2, 3, 4, 5] });\n  Object.defineProperty(navigator, 'languages', { get: () => ['zh-CN', 'zh'] });\n  Object.defineProperty(navigator, 'hardwareConcurrency', { get: () => 8 });\n  window.chrome = { runtime: {}, loadTimes: function(){}, csi: function(){}, app: {} };\n};\n\nasync function main() {\n  const cookies = JSON.parse(fs.readFileSync(COOKIES_FILE, 'utf8'));\n  const browser = await chromium.launch({ headless: true, args: ['--no-sandbox', '--disable-blink-features=AutomationControlled'] });\n  const ctx = await browser.newContext({ locale: 'zh-CN', viewport: { width: 1920, height: 1080 }, userAgent: 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; Win64; x64) AppleWebKit/537.36' });\n  await ctx.addCookies(cookies);\n  const page = await ctx.newPage();\n  await page.addInitScript(STEALTH_INIT);\n  \n  const url = `https://www.tapd.cn/${WORKSPACE_ID}/bugtrace/bugs/add`;\n  await page.goto(url, { waitUntil: 'domcontentloaded', timeout: 30000 }).catch(() => {});\n  await page.waitForTimeout(5000);\n  \n  const pageTitle = await page.title();\n  if (pageTitle.includes('WAF')) { console.log('WAF!'); await browser.close(); process.exit(1); }\n  \n  // Fill form\n  await page.fill('#BugTitle', '卡组私密无法选中');\n  await page.selectOption('#BugVersionReport', '【1V1】正式版本V2.0');\n  await page.selectOption('#BugModule', '1V1');\n  await page.selectOption('#BugPriority', 'P2');\n  \n  // Set handler via autocomplete\n  const input = page.locator('#BugCurrentOwnerValue');\n  await input.click();\n  await page.waitForTimeout(300);\n  await page.fill('#BugCurrentOwnerValue', '谭');\n  await page.waitForTimeout(2000);\n  \n  const sugg = page.locator('.tt-suggestion').first();\n  if (await sugg.isVisible()) {\n    await sugg.click();\n    await page.waitForTimeout(1000);\n  }\n  \n  const hv = await page.evaluate(() => ({\n    value: document.getElementById('BugCurrentOwner')?.value,\n    display: document.getElementById('BugCurrentOwnerValue')?.value,\n  }));\n  console.log('Handler:', JSON.stringify(hv));\n  \n  // Try submitting via JS form submit instead of clicking the button\n  console.log('Submitting via JS...');\n  \n  // Method 1: Click the hidden save_view via JS\n  await page.evaluate(() => {\n    const btn = document.getElementById('save_view');\n    if (btn) btn.click();\n  });\n  \n  await page.waitForTimeout(5000);\n  let resultUrl = page.url();\n  console.log('After JS click:', resultUrl);\n  \n  if (!resultUrl.includes('bugs/add')) {\n    console.log('SUCCESS!');\n    await page.screenshot({ path: path.join(__dirname, 'tapd_success.png') });\n    await browser.close();\n    return;\n  }\n  \n  // Method 2: Try clicking the real submit button (the hidden #save_return) directly\n  console.log('Method 2: Click save_return via JS...');\n  await page.evaluate(() => {\n    const btn = document.getElementById('save_return');\n    if (btn) btn.removeAttribute('class');\n    if (btn) btn.click();\n  });\n  await page.waitForTimeout(5000);\n  resultUrl = page.url();\n  console.log('After method 2:', resultUrl);\n  \n  if (!resultUrl.includes('bugs/add')) {\n    console.log('SUCCESS!');\n    await browser.close();\n    return;\n  }\n  \n  // Method 3: Try submitting the form directly\n  console.log('Method 3: Submit form directly...');\n  await page.evaluate(() => {\n    const form = document.querySelector('form');\n    if (form) {\n      // Find the save_view submit and click it\n      const saveView = form.querySelector('#save_view');\n      if (saveView) saveView.click();\n    }\n  });\n  await page.waitForTimeout(5000);\n  resultUrl = page.url();\n  console.log('After method 3:', resultUrl);\n  \n  if (!resultUrl.includes('bugs/add')) {\n    console.log('SUCCESS!');\n    await browser.close();\n    return;\n  }\n  \n  // Method 4: Use the anchor button #_view which calls the JS submit\n  console.log('Method 4: Click anchor #_view with force...');\n  await page.click('#_view', { force: true });\n  await page.waitForTimeout(5000);\n  resultUrl = page.url();\n  console.log('After method 4:', resultUrl);\n  \n  if (!resultUrl.includes('bugs/add')) {\n    console.log('SUCCESS!');\n    await browser.close();\n    return;\n  }\n  \n  // Check actual errors\n  const pageText = await page.evaluate(() => document.body.innerText.substring(0, 2000));\n  console.log('\\nPage text:', pageText);\n  await page.screenshot({ path: path.join(__dirname, 'tapd_error.png') });\n  \n  await browser.close();\n}\n\nmain().catch(e => { console.error('Fatal:', e.message); process.exit(1); });\n","path":"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\workspace\\tapd_create_bug4.mjs"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":561,"output":1655,"cacheRead":92800,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":95016,"cost":{"input":0.00007854,"output":0.00046340000000000004,"cacheRead":0.0025984,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00314034}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778849665131,"responseId":"15e26fc7-331b-48b6-9245-b343b94d8c9d"}}
