{"type":"message","id":"28629125","parentId":"05ca650e","timestamp":"2026-05-15T14:13:26.668Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Actually, wait. Let me think about this more carefully. The bug was already created with handler = 553342158. On the TAPD page it shows \"处理人: 553342158\" (raw ID), which means the TAPD system stored the ID but the UI didn't resolve it to a name.\n\nHowever, the bug IS assigned to user 553342158 (which is 谭佳钦). So functionally, the bug is already his - it's just that the UI shows the ID instead of the name.\n\nThe issue is that when I used `page.evaluate(() => { document.getElementById('BugCurrentOwner').value = '553342158' })`, I set the hidden field value but didn't trigger the TAPD JavaScript that resolves user IDs to display names. The autocomplete should handle this.\n\nFor the edit, I need to go to the bug edit page and properly use the autocomplete. But actually, maybe it's easier to just tell 小骑士 that the bug is already assigned to him (the system has his user ID), and the display name might just be a visual glitch. Or I can try to edit it.\n\nLet me just try running the fix script and see what happens. If it's too complicated, I'll just tell him the bug is his.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_m7lxaDGr6RpgZbbS1KJ82648","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\workspace; node tapd_fix_handler.mjs 2>&1","timeout":90}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":156,"output":356,"cacheRead":108544,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":109056,"cost":{"input":0.00002184,"output":0.00009968000000000001,"cacheRead":0.003039232,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0031607519999999997}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778854401728,"responseId":"f4ae5ba5-3000-47b7-a35c-2f6b8043bbee"}}
