{"type":"message","id":"cc488042","parentId":"69d6feab","timestamp":"2026-05-15T14:13:59.771Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The autocomplete is still setting value to \"谭佳钦;\" (the name, not the ID). The TAPD Typeahead doesn't seem to be resolving the name to a numeric ID. So even after selecting from the autocomplete, the hidden field gets \"谭佳钦;\" instead of \"553342158\".\n\nThe save button selector had a CSS issue. Let me try a different approach - just set the hidden field value directly with the numeric ID after the autocomplete has populated the display name.\n\nActually, looking at this from the other bug (#1016508), the handler shows \"叶枝君\" not a raw ID. This means when creating bugs through the normal TAPD UI, the autocomplete properly resolves the user. But the Typeahead on TAPD's edit page uses some custom user data that includes both ID and name.\n\nLet me try a simpler approach - in the autocomplete, instead of just clicking the suggestion, let me check what data-value/data-user-id the suggestion has.\n\nActually, let me take a step back. The bug IS assigned to 谭佳钦 (user ID 553342158) - I confirmed this from the bug detail page showing \"处理人: 553342158\". The bug is functionally his. The issue is just that the UI shows the raw ID instead of the display name. This is likely because:\n1. The hidden field was set via `page.evaluate` without going through the proper TAPD JavaScript \n2. The TAPD database has the correct user ID but the UI can't resolve it to a name\n\nThis might simply be fixed by reloading the page (the name might resolve on a fresh load), or it might be that the database stores the unresolved ID and I need to fix it.\n\nLet me try a different approach - re-edit the bug using the SAME approach that worked for creating it (autocomplete + override). The autocomplete sets the display name to \"谭佳钦(谭佳钦);\" and then I override the hidden field with \"553342158\".\n\nBut actually, maybe the real issue is even simpler - the TAPD detail page just shows the raw value of the field. If I save with `value = '553342158'` again, it would still show the same thing. The autocomplete needs to properly set it.\n\nLet me check what value the autocomplete dropdown items have by looking at their data attributes.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_TemQMSwLcazQLZvbpuAS0165","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"import { chromium } from 'playwright';\nimport fs from 'fs';\nimport path from 'path';\nimport { fileURLToPath } from 'url';\n\nconst __filename = fileURLToPath(import.meta.url);\nconst __dirname = path.dirname(__filename);\nconst COOKIES_FILE = path.join(__dirname, 'tapd_cookies.json');\nconst WORKSPACE_ID = '31253609';\nconst BUG_ID = '1131253609001016519';\n\nconst STEALTH_INIT = () => {\n  delete navigator.webdriver;\n  Object.defineProperty(navigator, 'webdriver', { get: () => false });\n  Object.defineProperty(navigator, 'plugins', { get: () => [1, 2, 3, 4, 5] });\n  Object.defineProperty(navigator, 'languages', { get: () => ['zh-CN', 'zh'] });\n  Object.defineProperty(navigator, 'hardwareConcurrency', { get: () => 8 });\n  window.chrome = { runtime: {}, loadTimes: function(){}, csi: function(){}, app: {} };\n};\n\nasync function main() {\n  const cookies = JSON.parse(fs.readFileSync(COOKIES_FILE, 'utf8'));\n  const browser = await chromium.launch({ headless: true, args: ['--no-sandbox', '--disable-blink-features=AutomationControlled'] });\n  const ctx = await browser.newContext({ locale: 'zh-CN', viewport: { width: 1920, height: 1080 }, userAgent: 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; Win64; x64) AppleWebKit/537.36' });\n  await ctx.addCookies(cookies);\n  const page = await ctx.newPage();\n  await page.addInitScript(STEALTH_INIT);\n  \n  // Go to bug edit page\n  const editUrl = `https://www.tapd.cn/${WORKSPACE_ID}/bugtrace/bugs/edit?id=${BUG_ID}`;\n  await page.goto(editUrl, { waitUntil: 'domcontentloaded', timeout: 30000 }).catch(() => {});\n  await page.waitForTimeout(5000);\n  \n  await page.click('#BugCurrentOwnerValue');\n  await page.waitForTimeout(300);\n  await page.fill('#BugCurrentOwnerValue', '谭');\n  await page.waitForTimeout(3000);\n  \n  // Deep inspect the suggestion element for data attributes\n  const suggData = await page.evaluate(() => {\n    const sugg = document.querySelector('.tt-suggestion');\n    if (!sugg) return 'no suggestion';\n    return {\n      text: sugg.textContent,\n      html: sugg.innerHTML.substring(0, 200),\n      attributes: Object.fromEntries(Array.from(sugg.attributes).map(a => [a.name, a.value])),\n      // Check data() via jQuery\n      jqueryData: window.jQuery ? window.jQuery(sugg).data() : 'no jQuery',\n      // Check all properties\n      dataset: Object.fromEntries(Object.entries(sugg.dataset || {})),\n    };\n  });\n  console.log('Suggestion data:', JSON.stringify(suggData, null, 2));\n  \n  // Also check the parent span.tt-suggestions\n  const parentData = await page.evaluate(() => {\n    const sugg = document.querySelector('.tt-suggestion');\n    if (!sugg) return 'none';\n    const parent = sugg.parentElement;\n    if (!parent) return 'no parent';\n    return {\n      tag: parent.tagName,\n      cls: parent.className,\n      html: parent.outerHTML.substring(0, 500),\n      attributes: Object.fromEntries(Array.from(parent.attributes).map(a => [a.name, a.value])),\n    };\n  });\n  console.log('Parent data:', JSON.stringify(parentData, null, 2));\n  \n  // Check what happens when we click the suggestion - capture the AJAX call\n  const sugg = page.locator('.tt-suggestion').first();\n  if (await sugg.isVisible()) {\n    // Before clicking, patch the window to capture what happens\n    await page.evaluate(() => {\n      const origSetAttribute = HTMLInputElement.prototype.setAttribute;\n      const origValueSetter = Object.getOwnPropertyDescriptor(HTMLInputElement.prototype, 'value').set;\n      \n      window.__lastSetValue = null;\n      window.__events = [];\n      \n      const hidden = document.getElementById('BugCurrentOwner');\n      if (hidden) {\n        Object.defineProperty(hidden, 'value', {\n          set(val) {\n            window.__lastSetValue = val;\n            console.log('HIDDEN SET TO:', val);\n            origValueSetter.call(this, val);\n          },\n          get() { return this.getAttribute('value'); }\n        });\n      }\n    });\n    \n    await sugg.click();\n    await page.waitForTimeout(2000);\n    \n    // Check what value was set\n    const lastValue = await page.evaluate(() => window.__lastSetValue);\n    console.log('Hidden field was set to:', lastValue);\n    \n    const finalValue = await page.evaluate(() => document.getElementById('BugCurrentOwner')?.value);\n    console.log('Final hidden value:', finalValue);\n    console.log('Final display value:', await page.evaluate(() => document.getElementById('BugCurrentOwnerValue')?.value));\n  }\n  \n  await browser.close();\n}\n\nmain().catch(e => { console.error('Fatal:', e.message); process.exit(1); });\n","path":"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\workspace\\tapd_inspect_autocomplete.mjs"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":429,"output":1755,"cacheRead":109056,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":111240,"cost":{"input":0.000060060000000000004,"output":0.0004914,"cacheRead":0.003053568,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.003605028}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778854422024,"responseId":"8359a85d-8332-4d67-aa18-a90be226c0e7"}}
