{"type":"message","id":"e30a8f64","parentId":"ef299832","timestamp":"2026-05-15T14:14:28.530Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I see the issue clearly!\n\nThe jQuery data for the suggestion is:\n```json\n{\n  \"ttDataset\": \"stats\",\n  \"ttValue\": \"谭佳钦(谭佳钦)\",\n  \"ttDatum\": {\n    \"show\": \"谭佳钦(谭佳钦)\",\n    \"value\": \"谭佳钦 tanjiaqin 谭佳钦\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\nThe `ttDatum.value` is `\"谭佳钦 tanjiaqin 谭佳钦\"` - it's a pinyin search string, NOT the user ID! The TAPD Typeahead only has the name/pinyin data, not the numeric user ID in its suggestions.\n\nWhen the suggestion is selected, the Typeahead sets the hidden field value to `\"谭佳钦;\"` (the name, not the user ID).\n\nThis means when I create a bug and set the handler via autocomplete, the hidden field contains the user's name, not their numeric ID. And when submitted, TAPD somehow resolves it.\n\nBut wait - the bug that was created was already submitted with `value = '553342158'` (overridden via page.evaluate), and it STILL showed the raw ID on the detail page.\n\nThis is confusing. Let me think about it differently:\n1. The normal way TAPD works: autocomplete → hidden field gets \"谭佳钦;name\" or \"553342158\" → form submits → TAPD backend stores it properly\n2. My override set `value = '553342158'` on the hidden field → form submitted → TAPD stored it as raw text \"553342158\"\n\nMaybe the autocomplete is supposed to set the hidden field to `\"谭佳钦(谭佳钦)\"` (the display format with parentheses) and TAPD's backend parses it out. The fact that the detail page shows \"553342158\" as raw text suggests the hidden field value was submitted as-is without going through the proper autocomplete format.\n\nLet me check what the autocomplete normally sets the value to when you select a user through the UI normally (not via my override). From the output: `value = \"谭佳钦;\"` - hmm, there's a semicolon.\n\nWait, maybe the format is: `\"user_name(user_display_name);\"` and TAPD parses the user ID from the semicolon-separated format? Or maybe TAPD has a different field that stores the actual ID.\n\nLet me check the first bug that was properly created. The first bug mentioned in the reference was #1016508 with handler \"叶枝君\" which showed properly. The autocomplete must be setting the field in a format that TAPD can parse.\n\nLet me check: when we create a new bug (in the first test), and I set the handler via autocomplete (no override), what value does the hidden field get? From the earlier tapd_create_bug3.mjs run, it was `value: \"谭佳钦;\"`. But when I submitted the form with that value (without branch field), it failed validation.\n\nWhen I submitted with `value = '553342158'` AND `branch = 'YYZY_1V1_V1.0'`, it succeeded but showed the raw ID.\n\nSo the solution might be: instead of setting the hidden field to the numeric ID, I should leave it as what the autocomplete set (`\"谭佳钦;\"`) and also fill the branch field. Let me try!\n\nActually wait, the CREATE flow already does this:\n- Autocomplete sets value to `\"谭佳钦;\"`\n- I then override to `\"553342158\"`\n- Submit succeeds\n\nLet me try again WITHOUT the override - just let the autocomplete set `\"谭佳钦;\"` and submit with ALL required fields.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"搞清楚了！TAPD 的 autocomplete 返回的是 `\"谭佳钦;\"` 格式（名字+分号），不是我之前强行塞的 `553342158`。问题是之前提交时我覆盖了隐藏域的值。让我重新试试，不走覆盖，用 autocomplete 的原始值提交。"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_2wlav6yAnJNUViyKSuBz1958","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\workspace; node tapd_fix_handler.mjs 2>&1","timeout":90}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":403,"output":953,"cacheRead":111488,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":112844,"cost":{"input":0.000056420000000000005,"output":0.00026684,"cacheRead":0.003121664,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0034449240000000002}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778854454463,"responseId":"85db6a05-6a38-486b-8600