{"type":"message","id":"7492250b","parentId":"dff87c59","timestamp":"2026-05-15T14:15:50.403Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_7CK8oYIwP8B0orl95YVj0104","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"    if (pageTitle.includes('WAF')) {\n      if (headless) {\n        console.log('WAF blocked in headless, retry with headless:false');\n        await browser.close();\n        return createBug({ ...options, headless: false });\n      }\n      throw new Error('WAF blocked - try again or use headed mode');\n    }\n    \n    // Fill fields\n    await page.fill('#BugTitle', title);\n    if (version) await page.selectOption('#BugVersionReport', version);\n    if (priority) await page.selectOption('#BugPriority', priority);\n    if (mod) await page.selectOption('#BugModule', mod);\n    if (branch) await page.selectOption('#BugCustomFieldOne', branch);\n    \n    if (handler) {\n      await page.evaluate((id) => {\n        const h = document.querySelector('#BugCurrentOwner');\n        if (h) { h.value = id; h.dispatchEvent(new Event('change', { bubbles: true })); }\n      }, handler);\n    }\n    \n    if (cc) {\n      await page.evaluate((id) => {\n        const c = document.querySelector('#BugCc');\n        if (c) { c.value = id; c.dispatchEvent(new Event('change', { bubbles: true })); }\n      }, cc);\n    }\n    \n    if (description) {\n      await page.evaluate((desc) => {\n        const d = document.querySelector('#BugDescription');\n        if (d) { d.value = desc; d.dispatchEvent(new Event('input', { bubbles: true })); }\n      }, description);\n    }\n    \n    // Submit\n    await page.evaluate(() => {\n      const btn = document.querySelector('#save_return');\n      if (btn) btn.click();\n    });\n    \n    await page.waitForTimeout(5000);\n    const resultUrl = page.url();\n    \n    if (!resultUrl.includes('bugtrace/bugs/add')) {\n      return resultUrl;\n    } else {\n      const errors = await page.evaluate(() => {\n\n[27 more lines in file. Use offset=120 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1778854550402}}
{"type":"message","id":"d9a21ff2","parentId":"7492250b","timestamp":"2026-05-15T14:16:01.203Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see the issue in the create_bug.mjs script. The handler field handling at line 86-90:\n```javascript\nif (handler) {\n  await page.evaluate((id) => {\n    const h = document.querySelector('#BugCurrentOwner');\n    if (h) { h.value = id; h.dispatchEvent(new Event('change', { bubbles: true })); }\n  }, handler);\n}\n```\n\nThis directly sets the hidden field value. The problem is that this removes the resolver/dispatcher format that the TAPD Typeahead would normally set (like \"谭佳钦;\"). \n\nThe fix should be:\n1. Type the handler name in the autocomplete input\n2. Wait for dropdown\n3. Click the suggestion\n4. DON'T override the hidden field value\n\nBut the skill function takes a `handler` parameter which is a user ID like \"1415287364\". If we use the autocomplete, we need the DISPLAY NAME instead.\n\nActually, looking at the TAPD autocomplete behavior more carefully:\n- When you type \"谭\" in the autocomplete field `#BugCurrentOwnerValue`\n- The dropdown shows suggestions with jQuery data: `{show: \"谭佳钦(谭佳钦)\", value: \"谭佳钦 tanjiaqin 谭佳钦\"}`\n- When you click a suggestion, the hidden field `#BugCurrentOwner` gets set to `\"谭佳钦;\"` (the name + semicolon)\n- The display field `#BugCurrentOwnerValue` gets set to `\"谭佳钦(谭佳钦);\"` (the display name)\n\nSo the format TAPD expects in the hidden field is `\"name;\"` (name with semicolon), not the numeric user ID! TAPD's backend resolves the name to a user ID.\n\nThis means the create_bug script should:\n1. Use the autocomplete by typing the user NAME\n2. Click the suggestion\n3. NOT set the hidden field value directly\n\nOr alternatively, if we want to set the value directly, set it as `\"谭佳钦;\"` format, not as numeric ID.\n\nLet me update the script to properly handle the handler using the autocomplete.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_GuLAy6iu7oMecxf5MMHd3411","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"~/.openclaw/plugin-skills/tapd-bug-create/scripts/create_bug.mjs","edits":[{"oldText":"    if (handler) {\n      await page.evaluate((id) => {\n        const h = document.querySelector('#BugCurrentOwner');\n        if (h) { h.value = id; h.dispatchEvent(new Event('change', { bubbles: true })); }\n      }, handler);\n    }","newText":"    if (handler) {\n      // Use the autocomplete to set handler - TAPD expects name format not raw ID\n      // handler param can be either a user ID (553342158) or a name (谭佳钦)\n      const isNumericId = /^\\d+$/.test(handler);\n      const searchName = isNumericId ? '' : handler;\n      \n      if (searchName) {\n        // Type name to trigger autocomplete, then select first result\n        await page.click('#BugCurrentOwnerValue');\n        await page.waitForTimeout(300);\n        await page.fill('#BugCurrentOwnerValue', searchName);\n        await page.waitForTimeout(2000);\n        \n        const sugg = page.locator('.tt-suggestion').first();\n        if (await sugg.isVisible()) {\n          await sugg.click();\n          await page.waitForTimeout(1000);\n        }\n      }\n      // If numeric ID was provided, we can't use it directly in the autocomplete\n      // In that case the caller should provide the display name\n    }"}]}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":465,"output":1006,"cacheRead":118144,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":119615,"cost":{"input":0.00006510000000000001,"output":0.00028168000000000003,"cacheRead":0.003308032,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.003654812}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778854550408,"responseId":"935443e5-a3d6-49fc-9166-c3ebd5edd8f1"}}
